Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{180%g} and cook, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.

Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into
small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Lower the heat to medium, then add the shallot, @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and
courgette to the lardons.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until the veg is softened and starting to brown,
~{4-5%mins}.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly.

Meanwhile, add the @linguine{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with oil
and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the @water{100%ml} for the sauce, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and
@Italian style herbs{1%tsp} to the bacon pan.

Stir and bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly
reduced, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and half the
@hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated), adding a splash of water if it's a
little thick.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce. Toss to coat well and season to taste with
salt and plenty of @ground black pepper{}.

Serve your bacon linguine in bowls sprinkled with the remaining cheese. Enjoy!

> Step 1 MOD: If you've chosen to double up on bacon lardons, cook the recipe
> in the same way.